33143 // VALIGNDZ128rmbi, VALIGNDZ128rmi, VALIGNDZ256rmbi, VALIGNDZ256rmi, VALI...
33144 printU8Imm(MI, 7, O);
33145 return;
33146 break;
33147 case 16:
33148 // VALIGNDZ128rri, VALIGNDZ256rri, VALIGNDZrri, VALIGNQZ128rri, VALIGNQZ2...
33149 printU8Imm(MI, 3, O);
33150 return;
33151 break;
33152 case 17:
33153 // VCVTDQ2PSZrrbk, VCVTPD2DQZrrbk, VCVTPD2PSZrrbk, VCVTPD2QQZrrbk, VCVTPD...
33154 printRoundingControl(MI, 4, O);
33155 return;
33156 break;
33157 case 18:
33158 // VFIXUPIMMPDZ128rmbi, VFIXUPIMMPDZ128rmi, VFIXUPIMMPDZ256rmbi, VFIXUPIM...
33159 printU8Imm(MI, 8, O);
33160 return;
33161 break;
33162 case 19:
33163 // VGF2P8AFFINEINVQBZ128rmbik, VGF2P8AFFINEINVQBZ256rmbik, VGF2P8AFFINEIN...
33164 printbytemem(MI, 4, O);
33165 break;
33166 case 20:
33167 // VGF2P8AFFINEINVQBZ128rmbikz, VGF2P8AFFINEINVQBZ256rmbikz, VGF2P8AFFINE...
33168 printbytemem(MI, 3, O);
33169 break;
33170 }
33171
33172
33173 // Fragment 7 encoded into 4 bits for 12 unique commands.
33174 switch ((Bits >> 50) & 15) {
33175 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid command number.");
33176 case 0:
33177 // V4FMADDPSrmk, V4FMADDPSrmkz, V4FMADDSSrmk, V4FMADDSSrmkz, V4FNMADDPSrm...
33178 return;
33179 break;
33180 case 1:
33181 // VAARG_64, VAARG_X32, VADDPDZrrbk, VADDPDZrrbkz, VADDPSZrrbk, VADDPSZrr...
33182 O << ", ";
33183 break;
33184 case 2:
33185 // VADDPDZ128rmbk, VADDPDZ128rmbkz, VANDNPDZ128rmbk, VANDNPDZ128rmbkz, VA...
33186 O << "{1to2}";
33187 return;
33188 break;
33189 case 3:
33190 // VADDPDZ256rmbk, VADDPDZ256rmbkz, VADDPSZ128rmbk, VADDPSZ128rmbkz, VAND...
33191 O << "{1to4}";
33192 return;
33193 break;
33194 case 4:
33195 // VADDPDZrmbk, VADDPDZrmbkz, VADDPSZ256rmbk, VADDPSZ256rmbkz, VANDNPDZrm...
33196 O << "{1to8}";
33197 return;
33198 break;
33199 case 5:
33200 // VADDPSZrmbk, VADDPSZrmbkz, VANDNPSZrmbk, VANDNPSZrmbkz, VANDPSZrmbk, V...
33201 O << "{1to16}";
33202 return;
33203 break;
33204 case 6:
33205 // VALIGNDZ128rmbik, VALIGNDZ128rmbikz, VALIGNQZ256rmbik, VALIGNQZ256rmbi...
33206 O << "{1to4}, ";
33207 break;
33208 case 7:
33209 // VALIGNDZ256rmbik, VALIGNDZ256rmbikz, VALIGNQZrmbik, VALIGNQZrmbikz, VC...
33210 O << "{1to8}, ";
33211 break;
33212 case 8:
33213 // VALIGNDZrmbik, VALIGNDZrmbikz, VCMPPSZrmbik, VFIXUPIMMPSZrmbik, VFIXUP...
33214 O << "{1to16}, ";
33215 break;
33216 case 9:
33217 // VALIGNQZ128rmbik, VALIGNQZ128rmbikz, VCMPPDZ128rmbik, VFIXUPIMMPDZ128r...
33218 O << "{1to2}, ";
33219 break;
33220 case 10:
33221 // VCMPPDZrribk, VCMPPSZrribk, VCMPSDZrrb_Intk, VCMPSSZrrb_Intk, VFIXUPIM...
33222 O << ", {sae}, ";
33223 break;
33224 case 11:
33225 // VCVTSS2SDZrrb_Intk, VCVTSS2SDZrrb_Intkz, VGETEXPSDZrbk, VGETEXPSDZrbkz...
33226 O << ", {sae}";
33227 return;
33228 break;
33229 }
33230
33231
33232 // Fragment 8 encoded into 3 bits for 7 unique commands.
33233 switch ((Bits >> 54) & 7) {
33234 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid command number.");
33235 case 0:
33236 // VAARG_64, VAARG_X32
33237 printOperand(MI, 8, O);
33238 return;
33239 break;
33240 case 1:
33241 // VADDPDZrrbk, VADDPSZrrbk, VADDSDZrrb_Intk, VADDSSZrrb_Intk, VCVTSD2SSZ...
33242 printRoundingControl(MI, 5, O);
33243 return;
33244 break;
33245 case 2:
33246 // VADDPDZrrbkz, VADDPSZrrbkz, VADDSDZrrb_Intkz, VADDSSZrrb_Intkz, VCVTSD...
33247 printRoundingControl(MI, 4, O);
33248 return;
33249 break;
33250 case 3:
33251 // VALIGNDZ128rmbik, VALIGNDZ128rmik, VALIGNDZ256rmbik, VALIGNDZ256rmik, ...
33252 printU8Imm(MI, 9, O);
33253 return;
33254 break;
33255 case 4:
33256 // VALIGNDZ128rmbikz, VALIGNDZ128rmikz, VALIGNDZ256rmbikz, VALIGNDZ256rmi...
33257 printU8Imm(MI, 8, O);
33258 return;
33259 break;
33260 case 5:
33261 // VALIGNDZ128rrik, VALIGNDZ256rrik, VALIGNDZrrik, VALIGNQZ128rrik, VALIG...
33262 printU8Imm(MI, 5, O);
33263 return;
33264 break;
33265 case 6:
33266 // VALIGNDZ128rrikz, VALIGNDZ256rrikz, VALIGNDZrrikz, VALIGNQZ128rrikz, V...
33267 printU8Imm(MI, 4, O);
33268 return;
33269 break;
33270 }

33272}

33587#undef PRINT_ALIAS_INSTR
33588
33589bool X86IntelInstPrinter::printAliasInstr(const MCInst *MI, uint64_t Address, raw_ostream &OS) {
33590 static const PatternsForOpcode OpToPatterns[] = {
33591 {X86::AAD8i8, 0, 1 },
33592 {X86::AAM8i8, 1, 1 },
33593 {X86::XSTORE, 2, 1 },
33594 };
33595
33596 static const AliasPattern Patterns[] = {
33597 // X86::AAD8i8 - 0
33598 {0, 0, 1, 1 },
33599 // X86::AAM8i8 - 1
33600 {4, 1, 1, 1 },
33601 // X86::XSTORE - 2
33602 {8, 2, 0, 0 },
33603 };
33604
33605 static const AliasPatternCond Conds[] = {
33606 // (AAD8i8 10) - 0
33607 {AliasPatternCond::K_Imm, uint32_t(10)},
33608 // (AAM8i8 10) - 1
33609 {AliasPatternCond::K_Imm, uint32_t(10)},
33610 // (XSTORE) - 2
33611 };
33612
33613 static const char AsmStrings[] =
33614 /* 0 */ "aad\0"
33615 /* 4 */ "aam\0"
33616 /* 8 */ "xstorerng\0"
33617 ;
33618
33619#ifndef NDEBUG
33620 static struct SortCheck {
33621 SortCheck(ArrayRef<PatternsForOpcode> OpToPatterns) {
33622 assert(std::is_sorted(
33623 OpToPatterns.begin(), OpToPatterns.end(),
33624 [](const PatternsForOpcode &L, const PatternsForOpcode &R) {
33625 return L.Opcode < R.Opcode;
33626 }) &&
33627 "tablegen failed to sort opcode patterns");
33628 }
33629 } sortCheckVar(OpToPatterns);
33630#endif
33631
33632 AliasMatchingData M {
33633 makeArrayRef(OpToPatterns),
33634 makeArrayRef(Patterns),
33635 makeArrayRef(Conds),
33636 StringRef(AsmStrings, array_lengthof(AsmStrings)),
33637 nullptr,
33638 };
33639 const char *AsmString = matchAliasPatterns(MI, nullptr, M);
33640 if (!AsmString) return false;
33641
33642 unsigned I = 0;
33643 while (AsmString[I] != ' ' && AsmString[I] != '\t' &&
33644 AsmString[I] != '$' && AsmString[I] != '\0')
33645 ++I;
33646 OS << '\t' << StringRef(AsmString, I);
33647 if (AsmString[I] != '\0') {
33648 if (AsmString[I] == ' ' || AsmString[I] == '\t') {
33649 OS << '\t';
33650 ++I;
33651 }
33652 do {
33653 if (AsmString[I] == '$') {
33654 ++I;
33655 if (AsmString[I] == (char)0xff) {
33656 ++I;
33657 int OpIdx = AsmString[I++] - 1;
33658 int PrintMethodIdx = AsmString[I++] - 1;
33659 printCustomAliasOperand(MI, Address, OpIdx, PrintMethodIdx, OS);
33660 } else
33661 printOperand(MI, unsigned(AsmString[I++]) - 1, OS);
33662 } else {
33663 OS << AsmString[I++];
33664 }
33665 } while (AsmString[I] != '\0');
33666 }
33667
33668 return true;
33669}
33670
33671void X86IntelInstPrinter::printCustomAliasOperand(
33672 const MCInst *MI, uint64_t Address, unsigned OpIdx,
33673 unsigned PrintMethodIdx,
33674 raw_ostream &OS) {
33675 llvm_unreachable("Unknown PrintMethod kind");
33676}
